HEADWORD: Chemitype
<hw>Chem"i*type</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Chemi</ets>cal + <ets>-type</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Engraving)</fld> <def>One of a number of processes by which an
impression from an engraved plate is obtained in relief, to be used for
printing on an ordinary printing press.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

